
4. Validate Parentheses (with extensions)
Problem Given a string containing ()[]{}, determine if it’s valid.
Example
"{[()]}" → true
"{[(])}" → false
What Netflix is testing
* Stack usage
* Mapping relationships
* Defensive coding
Strong signals
* “Early exit on invalid state”
* “Stack must be empty at the end”
* Tests: empty string, odd length, only opening brackets


Time: O(n) — iterate string once

Space: O(n) — worst-case all openings on stack


Common Mistakes

Forgetting to check if stack is empty before popping

Only counting total openings/closings → fails for order

Handling only () → misses [] or {}

🧠 How it works

Stack stores currently open brackets.

When we see a closing bracket, it must match the last open bracket (stack.pop).

After processing, the stack must be empty if the string is valid.

Rules:

Every opening bracket has a corresponding closing bracket of the same type.

Brackets must close in the correct order.